00:39:04,620 --> 00:39:05,620
Nan Chu.

708
00:39:06,300 --> 00:39:07,500
In times of peace,

709
00:39:08,260 --> 00:39:10,810
being a firefighter is one of the most dangerous jobs.

710
00:39:12,420 --> 00:39:14,060
On the day the explosion happened,

711
00:39:14,980 --> 00:39:17,330
we had a brush with death too.

712
00:39:18,860 --> 00:39:20,140
We survived

713
00:39:20,780 --> 00:39:22,100
not because

714
00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:24,700
we were abler than them,

715
00:39:26,420 --> 00:39:27,700
but because we arrived later than them.

716
00:39:29,930 --> 00:39:31,260
But even so,

717
00:39:31,900 --> 00:39:33,620
Zhengang lost a leg.

718
00:39:36,300 --> 00:39:38,060
Behind every martyr,

719
00:39:38,740 --> 00:39:40,340
there is a broken family.

720
00:39:43,260 --> 00:39:45,540
When Captain Meng was the commander,

721
00:39:45,980 --> 00:39:46,980
he kept saying

722
00:39:47,820 --> 00:39:49,060
that if we sweated more during the training,

723
00:39:49,580 --> 00:39:50,890
we could bleed less in emergencies.

724
00:39:52,420 --> 00:39:53,610
After I became the director,

725
00:39:54,340 --> 00:39:56,130
I said that a lot too.

726
00:39:57,140 --> 00:39:57,900
I believe

727
00:39:58,340 --> 00:40:00,220
that when my students become mentors,

728
00:40:01,140 --> 00:40:02,180
they'll say that as well.

729
00:40:03,380 --> 00:40:04,940
But actually, we all know

730
00:40:06,420 --> 00:40:08,460
that no matter how long we train

731
00:40:09,260 --> 00:40:10,010
and how hard we train,

732
00:40:11,260 --> 00:40:12,530
when faced with disasters,

733
00:40:13,940 --> 00:40:15,420
we're just flesh and blood.

734
00:40:16,460 --> 00:40:18,260
No one can avoid death.

735
00:40:21,420 --> 00:40:22,170
Nan Chu.

736
00:40:23,060 --> 00:40:24,460
I said so much to you

737
00:40:27,540 --> 00:40:29,460
because I want you to think it over.

738
00:40:30,820 --> 00:40:31,700
I've made up my mind.

739
00:40:33,620 --> 00:40:35,140
If you choose me,

740
00:40:36,900 --> 00:40:38,460
we'll definitely spend more time apart than together.

741
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:40,340
Then I should cherish

742
00:40:40,340 --> 00:40:42,060
every moment when I'm with you.

743
00:40:43,300 --> 00:40:45,020
You also have to brace yourself

744
00:40:45,980 --> 00:40:47,300
for losing me.

745
00:40:49,820 --> 00:40:51,210
Don't worry about me.

746
00:40:51,980 --> 00:40:53,580
If you really died,

747
00:40:53,820 --> 00:40:55,410
I could take good care of myself.

748
00:40:56,100 --> 00:40:57,930
I've been living alone since I was young.

749
00:40:58,100 --> 00:40:59,140
I'm used to it.

750
00:41:03,980 --> 00:41:05,140
Sometimes,

751
00:41:07,460 --> 00:41:09,010
death is not the scariest thing.

752
00:41:17,740 --> 00:41:18,580
I understand.

753
00:41:19,100 --> 00:41:20,100
I really do.

754
00:41:21,940 --> 00:41:24,170
I don't want you to be everyone's hero.

755
00:41:25,780 --> 00:41:27,460
You protect the world.

756
00:41:28,460 --> 00:41:29,660
I protect you.

757
00:41:39,180 --> 00:41:39,980
Nan Chu.

758
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:42,580
The last time

759
00:41:43,020 --> 00:41:44,820
I made an oath under the national flag

760
00:41:46,180 --> 00:41:47,780
was when I joined the fire department.

761
00:41:52,140 --> 00:41:53,260
I volunteer to join

762
00:41:54,020 --> 00:41:55,940
the national fire and rescue team.

763
00:41:56,260 --> 00:41:57,260
I pledge unwavering loyalty to the Party,

764
00:41:57,620 --> 00:41:58,500
strict adherence to discipline,

765
00:41:59,060 --> 00:42:00,260
and willingness to face any challenge

766
00:42:00,260 --> 00:42:01,220
in the service of our society.

767
00:42:02,180 --> 00:42:03,140
I'm committed

768
00:42:03,820 --> 00:42:04,690
to obeying orders,

769
00:42:05,260 --> 00:42:06,300
following commands,

770
00:42:06,780 --> 00:42:07,700
fulfilling my duties diligently,

771
00:42:08,420 --> 00:42:09,530
honing my skills,

772
00:42:10,810 --> 00:42:11,740
fearlessly facing danger,

773
00:42:12,380 --> 00:42:13,290
and willingly making sacrifices.

774
00:42:13,980 --> 00:42:16,650
I'll dedicate my life to safeguarding the lives

775
00:42:16,900 --> 00:42:18,220
 and property of the people

776
00:42:18,980 --> 00:42:20,500
and maintaining social stability.

777
00:42:23,900 --> 00:42:25,290
That's my promise to the country.

778
00:42:26,940 --> 00:42:27,660
This

779
00:42:29,060 --> 00:42:30,330
is my promise to you.

780
00:42:34,430 --> 00:42:37,290
[Tips for Fire Safety]

781
00:42:37,290 --> 00:42:39,370
A smoke hood is an essential piece

782
00:42:39,370 --> 00:42:40,900
of personal protective equipment

783
00:42:40,900 --> 00:42:41,980
in both public spaces and residential areas.

784
00:42:41,980 --> 00:42:43,620
It plays a crucial role

785
00:42:43,620 --> 00:42:45,060
 in protecting our respiratory system,

786
00:42:45,060 --> 00:42:46,540
as well as our face and skin.

787
00:42:46,540 --> 00:42:48,340
Now, let us show you

788
00:42:48,340 --> 00:42:50,540
how to correctly use a smoke hood.

789
00:42:54,620 --> 00:42:56,130
First, open the packaging.

790
00:43:02,740 --> 00:43:04,460
Take out the mask.

791
00:43:07,020 --> 00:43:08,860
Make sure it's intact.

792
00:43:08,860 --> 00:43:10,540
Poke or tear open

793
00:43:12,420 --> 00:43:14,740
the sealing tabs on both sides.

794
00:43:23,860 --> 00:43:26,300
Next, put your hand into the mask,

795
00:43:26,300 --> 00:43:27,700
spread your fingers,

796
00:43:27,980 --> 00:43:29,530
and give it three tugs to unfold it.

797
00:43:29,820 --> 00:43:31,540
Now, put on the mask.

798
00:43:34,380 --> 00:43:35,380
After putting it on,

799
00:43:35,380 --> 00:43:36,980
make sure

800
00:43:36,980 --> 00:43:38,170
you have no difficulty breathing.

801
00:43:38,780 --> 00:43:39,580
For those with long hair,

802
00:43:39,580 --> 00:43:41,740
be sure to tie it back

803
00:43:41,740 --> 00:43:42,860
to ensure the mask

804
00:43:42,860 --> 00:43:44,130
covers your hair.

805
00:43:44,130 --> 00:43:45,860
If the mask has straps,

806
00:43:45,860 --> 00:43:47,420
tie them

807
00:43:47,420 --> 00:43:48,340
tight

808
00:43:48,340 --> 00:43:50,130
for a snug fit.

809
00:43:51,740 --> 00:43:52,500
Remember,

810
00:43:52,500 --> 00:43:54,460
a smoke hood provides protection

811
00:43:54,460 --> 00:43:55,380
for about half an hour.

812
00:43:55,380 --> 00:43:57,420
Utilize this time wisely for a safe evacuation.

813
00:43:57,420 --> 00:43:58,700
Do you know how to use it now?
